Always-Less-Effort method

Method and relative algorithm to obtain a schedule of workload
in a descending linear way with user-defined parameters to set the rate between the work at the begin and at the end of the process.
This method allows to conserve the constraint of performing all the work into the pre-established days together with imposing a personal increase of the initial work with respect to the final work.
Algorithms, use cases, output example and mathematical formulations are provided.

Related app based on this algorithm is introduced ( https://getstudysprint.com/ ).

